saddle /ˈsædəl/

(saddling,saddled,saddles) 

1. N-COUNT A saddle is a leather seat that you put on the back of an animal so that you can ride the animal. 鞍 

2. V-T If you saddle a horse, you put a saddle on it so that you can ride it. 给 (马) 配鞍 

例： Why don't we saddle a couple of horses and go for a ride? 为什么我们不给几匹马配上鞍骑着转转？ 

3. PHRASAL VERB Saddle up means the same as . 同(saddle) 

例： I want to be gone from here as soon as we can saddle up. 我想一配好鞍就离开这儿。 

4. N-COUNT A saddle is a seat on a bicycle or motorcycle. (自行车或摩托车的) 车座

